		<td><b>PCE/TG16 emulator recommendation</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />What PC-Engine/TurboGrafx-16 emulator (if any) do most of you use? I'm trying to decide between Hu-Go! and Mednafen. The problem is that I haven't heard many people vouch for Hu-Go!'s emulation accuracy, while Mednafen is a multi-system emulator (and I already have separate emulators for practically all the other systems). The emulator needs to be free (but not necessarily <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Free_software" class="postlink">free software</a>), so Magic Engine is out. Any suggestions? (Chirs Covell, I'm guessing you're the expert on this?)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>ccovell</b> [ Tue Aug 22, 2006 7:33 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I use YAME and Magic Engine, mainly.  Mednafen is growing on me, simply because it's more accurate than the others.  If you're a programmer, an emu named "Neco" is also very useful, since it has VRAM, Palette, and memory viewers.  It does, however, have very low compatibility.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


